l Rules"},"603":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-9","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users","content":"Product analytics needs to connect anonymous pre-login behavior with known users after signup or login. The browser SDK starts with an anonymous distinct ID. When you know who the user is, call `identify` with a stable user ID."},"604":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-10","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users","content":"For exact SDK signatures, see the SDK reference. For backend identity payloads, see the API reference."},"605":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-11","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"Every event has a `distinct_id`. In the browser, the SDK creates one automatically and stores it using the configured persistence layer. Backend events must provide a `distinct_id` directly."},"606":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-12","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"The ingest service resolves each `distinct_id` to a `person_id` globally within the deployment:"},"607":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-13","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"If the distinct ID already exists in `person_distinct_ids`, the existing `person_id` is used."},"608":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-14","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"If it does not exist, a deterministic `person_id` is derived from the distinct ID."},"609":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-15","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"Every accepted event writes or refreshes the event distinct ID in `person_distinct_ids`."},"610":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-16","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"`$identify` and `$create_alias` also link additional anonymous or alias IDs to the same `person_id`."},"611":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-17","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"Use stable database IDs, account IDs, or UUIDs as identified user IDs. Avoid temporary IDs, emails that can change, or values such as `anonymous`, `guest`, `unknown`, `true`, `false`, or `null`."},"612":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-18","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#browser-identify","content":"Call `identify` after login or signup:"},"613":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-19","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#browser-identify","content":"This emits a `$identify` event. If the browser was previously anonymous, the event includes `$anon_distinct_id` so the ingest service can link the old anonymous ID and the new known ID to the same person."},"614":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-20","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#backend-identify","content":"You can identify users through the direct API by sending `$identify`:"},"615":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-21","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#backend-identify","content":"Backend services do not have automatic anonymous browser state. Use backend identify when a server process learns that two IDs should refer to the same person or when you need to update person properties from server-side facts."},"616":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-22","page_id":"/start/identify